Description: Drop PEP 728 `extra_items=object` from DynamicAgentConfigParam
 `google/genai/_interactions/types/dynamic_agent_config_param.py`
 declares a `TypedDict` with `extra_items=object`, the PEP 728 keyword
 argument that lets a `TypedDict` advertise an arbitrary-key shape to
 static checkers. PEP 728 lands in Python 3.13 and in
 typing-extensions 4.13; Noble ships typing-extensions 4.10, which
 raises
 `TypeError: _TypedDictMeta.__new__() got an unexpected keyword
 argument 'extra_items'` at module import time and breaks every
 downstream `from google import genai`.
 .
 The keyword is purely a type-checker hint — it has no runtime
 semantics, and `TypedDict` already accepts arbitrary keys at runtime
 — so dropping it leaves the runtime behaviour identical. The
 trailing `# type: ignore[call-arg]` comment, originally there to
 silence type checkers on Python releases below 3.13, becomes dead
 weight and is removed alongside.
Author: Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-21

--- a/google/genai/_interactions/types/dynamic_agent_config_param.py
+++ b/google/genai/_interactions/types/dynamic_agent_config_param.py
@@ -22,7 +22,7 @@
 __all__ = ["DynamicAgentConfigParam"]


-class DynamicAgentConfigParam(TypedDict, total=False, extra_items=object):  # type: ignore[call-arg]
+class DynamicAgentConfigParam(TypedDict, total=False):
     """Configuration for dynamic agents."""

     type: Required[Literal["dynamic"]]
